properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 3 at 3:33AM CST until February 4 at 6:00AM CST by NWS North Platte NE
properties.description:
...LIGHT SNOW IS ON THE WAY...

.A strong winter storm across the Rockies will reach into western
Nebraska and produce light snow this afternoon through Tuesday
morning.

* WHAT...Snow is expected with total snow accumulations of 1 to 3
inches.

* WHERE...Sheridan and Western Cherry Counties.

* WHEN...From noon CST /11 AM MST/ today to 6 AM CST /5 AM MST/
Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous
conditions could impact the evening commute.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Wind chill readings near zero are likely
Tuesday morning.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

Call Nebraska 511 for the latest road information.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM NOON CST /11 AM MST/ TODAY TO 6 AM CST /5 AM MST/ TUESDAY
